description:
Insecurity is as important to understanding our world as inequality. But unlike inequality, it is understudied, undertheorized, and underdiscussed. This book is an attempt to address the gap in literature.&nbsp;
The premise is that in reality, the status quo isn’t really working for anyone, even the affluent and comparatively privileged; and contrary to their convictions, it isn’t working for those fighting, sometimes violently, to retain their relative advantage in a rapidly changing world. They, too, are deeply insecure.&nbsp;
This is a book that will appeal to anyone trying to understand the current social and political moment and activists/organizers who want to be more effective.
